# Project: vdi_wrapper (VDI C++ Wrapper)
# --------------------- QUICK START FOR AI AGENTS --------------------------
# This is a native C++ SQL Server VDI (Virtual Device Interface) streaming
# library for backup pipeline instrumentation.
#
# Key files to understand first:
#   1. include/vdi_client.h     — Main class interface + SessionState machine
#   2. src/vdi_client.cpp       — Command loop, hardening, state transitions
#   3. include/sqlvdi.h         — COM interface definitions (critical vtable)
#   4. include/metrics.h        — Throughput + latency tracking
#   5. include/sink.h           — Pluggable output sink (NullSink|FileSink)
#   6. include/error_utils.h    — HRESULT translation + SessionState enum
#   7. docs/operational-behavior.md — Shutdown, timeout, retry, cleanup docs
#
# Build (MSVC x64, from repo root):
#   vcvars64.bat  # from VS install
#   cl src\*.cpp /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude
#   link *.obj /OUT:vdi_wrapper.exe ole32.lib /SUBSYSTEM:CONSOLE
#
# VDI protocol flow: CreateEx → GetConfiguration(blocking) → OpenDevice
#                     → command_loop(GetCommand→CompleteCommand) → VD_E_CLOSE
# Key gotcha: IClientVirtualDeviceSet2 inherits IClientVirtualDeviceSet
#             (8 methods), NOT IUnknown directly. Wrong vtable = ESP crash.
# --------------------- END QUICK START ------------------------------------

# 1. include/vdi_client.h
#    - Provides the VdiClient class interface.
#    - On Windows builds includes <windows.h>, <sqlvdi.h>, and <combaseapi.h>.
#    - Defines a placeholder implementation for non‑Windows platforms to allow
#      compilation without the actual VDI SDK.
#    - Exposes:
#        * SessionState state tracking (INIT→CONNECTED→STREAMING→FLUSHING→CLOSED/FAILED)
#        * bool connect(const std::wstring&, int);
#        * bool open_devices();
#        * void process_commands();        // Main command loop
#        * void close();                   // Idempotent cleanup
#        * void set_command_timeout(ms);   // Configurable GetCommand timeout
#        * SessionState state() const;     // Public state accessor
#        * FaultInjector& fault_injector(); // Testing hooks
#    - Private:
#        * bool handle_command(IClientVirtualDevice*, VDC_Command*);
#        * bool validate_write_command(const VDC_Command*);
#        * void check_stall(uint64_t now_us);
#        * devices_closed_ flag for idempotent close
#        * command_timeout_ms_ (default 30s)
#        * Stall detection: last_command_us_, last_bytes_total_, last_stall_warn_us_
#        * Resource accounting: active_buffers_, max_active_buffers_
#        * FaultInjector fault_injector_ (compile-time gated)
#    - Configuration constants:
#        * BUFFER_POOL_SIZE = 64
#        * BUFFER_SIZE = 64 KB
#        * DEFAULT_COMMAND_TIMEOUT_MS = 30000
#        * STALL_WARN_MS = 60000

# 2. src/vdi_client.cpp
#    - Implements VdiClient with all hardening (Day 15).
#    - Session state machine guards every public method:
#        * connect(): INIT → CONNECTED | FAILED
#        * open_devices(): CONNECTED → STREAMING | FAILED
#        * process_commands(): STREAMING → FLUSHING | FAILED
#        * close(): any → CLOSED (idempotent)
#    - Windows path:
#        * Calls CoInitializeEx(COINIT_MULTITHREADED).
#        * Uses CoCreateInstance to obtain CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet.
#        * Configures VDConfig (all 11 fields) and calls device_set_->CreateEx().
#        * Returns true on success.
#    - Non‑Windows path:
#        * Returns true as a stub.
#    - process_commands() (refactored 2026-05-17):
#        * Uses configurable timeout (command_timeout_ms_) instead of INFINITE.
#        * Handles VD_E_CLOSE as graceful shutdown (flush sink → close).
#        * Handles VD_E_TIMEOUT with stall detection (no abort).
#        * Validates VDC_Write commands before processing.
#        * Checks sink->is_open() and sink->write() return value.
#        * Fault injection hook after CompleteCommand.
#        * Resource accounting (active_buffers_ high-water mark).
#        * Post-loop: calls close() if in FLUSHING state.
#        * After loop exits calls metrics_.print_summary() + metrics_.to_json().
#    - handle_command():
#        * Switch on cmd->commandCode for VDC_Read, VDC_Write, VDC_Flush,
#          VDC_ClearError, VDC_Close.
#        * VDC_Write records chunk size metrics and buffer pool instrumentation.
#        * Actual sink write happens in process_commands() for independent timing.
#    - validate_write_command():
#        * Defensive checks: non-null cmd, non-null buffer, size > 0, size < 1GB.
#    - check_stall():
#        * Logs warnings when no byte progress for STALL_WARN_MS (60s).
#    - Destructor auto-cleanup: calls close() if not already done.

# 3. include/error_utils.h / src/error_utils.cpp (added 2026-05-17)
#    - SessionState enum: INIT, CONNECTED, STREAMING, FLUSHING, CLOSED, FAILED
#    - session_state_to_string() for logging
#    - hresult_to_string() maps HRESULT to human-readable text
#    - Covers all VDI protocol error codes + common COM errors

# 4. include/fault_injector.h / src/fault_injector.cpp (added 2026-05-17)
#    - Compile-time gated (FAULT_INJECTION_ENABLED, default 0)
#    - Two modes: fail after N chunks, fail next command
#    - Zero-cost stub when disabled (no state, no branches)

# 5. src/main.cpp
#    - Entry point for the application.
#    - Uses VdiClient directly:
#        * Generates a unique VDI device name with process ID suffix.
#        * Calls client.connect() then client.open_devices().
#        * Prints instructions for the T-SQL BACKUP command the user must run.
#        * Calls client.process_commands() to handle the backup data flow.
#        * Calls client.close() after completion.

# 6. include/sqlvdi_guids.h
#    - Declares CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet and IID_IClientVirtualDeviceSet2
#      using EXTERN_C const with <guiddef.h>.
#    - Can be included from any file that needs these GUID symbols.

# 7. src/sqlvdi_guids.cpp
#    - Defines the GUIDs via DEFINE_GUID() under #define INITGUID.
#    - Only file in the project that ever #defines INITGUID, preventing
#      multiple-definition linker errors.
#    - Replaces the old sqlvdi.cpp which used brace initialization instead
#      of the standard Windows DEFINE_GUID/INITGUID pattern.

# 8. CMakeLists.txt
#    - Sets C++17 standard.
#    - Includes the 'include' directory.
#    - Builds the vdi_wrapper executable from the source files:
#        * src/main.cpp, src/vdi_client.cpp, src/file_sink.cpp
#        * src/metrics.cpp, src/buffer_pool.cpp, src/sqlvdi_guids.cpp
#        * src/error_utils.cpp, src/fault_injector.cpp
#    - Three build configurations: vdi_wrapper (default), vdi_wrapper_no_logging,
#      vdi_wrapper_info, vdi_wrapper_debug
#    - Links against ole32.lib (required for COM on Windows).

# 9. Build notes
#    - On Windows, the project must be built with a compiler that can locate
#      the VDI SDK headers (vdi.h) and libraries.
#    - On non‑Windows platforms the placeholder definitions allow the code to
#      compile, but the VDI functionality will be a no‑op.
#    - CMake build may not be functional on all machines (2026-05-14).
#      Use manual MSVC cl.exe commands (see section 16) instead.

# 10. GUID Architecture (refactored 2026-05-09, IID corrected 2026-05-13)
#     - GUIDs are declared in include/sqlvdi_guids.h (EXTERN_C const with <guiddef.h>)
#       and defined in src/sqlvdi_guids.cpp (single #define INITGUID + DEFINE_GUID).
#     - This avoids:
#         * Multiple-definition linker errors (only one .cpp ever defines INITGUID)
#         * Header pollution (consumers only see extern declarations)
#         * Fragile brace-initialization (the old sqlvdi.cpp approach)
#     - GUID values (CRITICAL: IID and CLSID are DIFFERENT GUIDs):
#         CLSID_MSSQL_ClientVirtualDeviceSet = {0x40700425,0x0080,0x11d2,{0x85,0x1f,0x00,0xc0,0x4f,0xc2,0x17,0x59}}
#         IID_IClientVirtualDeviceSet2        = {0xd0e6eb07,0x7a62,0x11d2,{0x85,0x73,0x00,0xc0,0x4f,0xc2,0x17,0x59}}
#         IID_IClientVirtualDevice            = {0x40700424,0x0080,0x11d2,{0x85,0x1f,0x00,0xc0,0x4f,0xc2,0x17,0x59}}
#         IID_IClientVirtualDeviceSet         = {0x40700425,0x0080,0x11d2,{0x85,0x1f,0x00,0xc0,0x4f,0xc2,0x17,0x59}}

# 11. CreateEx Signature Fix (critical 2026-05-13)
#      - WRONG: CreateEx(LPCWSTR lpName, VDConfig* pConfig) - TWO parameters
#      - RIGHT: CreateEx(LPCWSTR lpInstanceName, LPCWSTR lpName, VDConfig* pConfig) - THREE parameters
#      - First parameter is the SQL Server instance name (nullptr for default instance)
#      - Calling with wrong signature causes VD_E_NOTSUPPORTED (0x80770009)
#      - Fixed in include/sqlvdi.h and src/vdi_client.cpp

# 12. VDConfig Structure Complete Definition (critical 2026-05-13)
#      - WRONG: Only 3 fields (deviceCount, features, commandTimeout)
#      - RIGHT: 11 fields as per MS SQL Server VDI specification
#      All required fields:
#        - deviceCount: Number of virtual devices
#        - features: Feature flags (VDF_Default = 0)
#        - prefixZoneSize, alignment, softFileMarkBlockSize, EOMWarningSize
#        - serverTimeOut: 60000 (60 seconds)
#        - blockSize: 64 KB, maxIODepth, maxTransferSize, bufferAreaSize
#      - Incomplete structure causes VD_E_INVALID (0x80770006)

# 13. IClientVirtualDeviceSet2 Vtable Layout Fix (CRITICAL 2026-05-13)
#      - ROOT CAUSE of "Run-Time Check Failure: ESP not properly saved" error
#      - WRONG: interface IClientVirtualDeviceSet2 : public IUnknown
#        (CreateEx at slot 3, but actual implementation expects it at slot 11)
#      - RIGHT: interface IClientVirtualDeviceSet2 : public IClientVirtualDeviceSet
#        (inherits 8 methods from IClientVirtualDeviceSet → CreateEx at slot 11)
#      - The real VDI interface chain:
#        IUnknown → IClientVirtualDeviceSet (8 methods) → IClientVirtualDeviceSet2 (2 methods)
#      - Wrong vtable offset causes mismatched stack cleanup → ESP corruption → RTC failure

# 14. VDI Protocol Flow (2026-05-13, hardened 2026-05-17)
#      - Proper sequence:
#        1. CoCreateInstance(CLSID, IID_IClientVirtualDeviceSet2)
#        2. device_set_->CreateEx(nullptr, lpName, &config)
#        3. device_set_->GetConfiguration(timeout, &server_config) — BLOCKS for SQL
#        4. device_set_->OpenDevice(name, &device) — for each device
#        5. device->GetCommand(timeout_ms, &cmd) — blocks for commands
#        6. Process command (VDC_Write, VDC_Flush, VDC_ClearError, etc.)
#        7. device->CompleteCommand(cmd, status, bytes, position) — 4 args!
#        8. Repeat 5-7 until GetCommand returns VD_E_CLOSE (0x80770001).
#      - SQL Server IO error 995 = VDI client dropped the connection.

# 15. Session State Machine (added 2026-05-17)
#      ┌──────┐    connect()     ┌───────────┐  open_devices()  ┌───────────┐
#      │ INIT │ ═══════════════> │ CONNECTED │ ════════════════> │ STREAMING │
#      └──────┘                  └───────────┘                   └─────┬─────┘
#          │                        │                            VD_E_CLOSE │
#          │                        │                                ▼
#          ▼                        ▼                          ┌───────────┐
#      ┌───────┐              ┌───────┐                       │ FLUSHING  │
#      │ FAILED│              │ FAILED│                       └─────┬─────┘
#      └───────┘              └───────┘                            │ close()
#          │                        │                              ▼
#          └────────── all roads lead to ──────────→         ┌──────────┐
#                                                           │  CLOSED  │
#                                                           └──────────┘

# 16. Compilation commands (MSVC x64, run from repo root):
#       vcvars64.bat  # from "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\18\Community\VC\Auxiliary\Build\"
#       cl src\sqlvdi_guids.cpp /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fosqlvdi_guids.obj
#       cl src\error_utils.cpp  /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Foerror_utils.obj
#       cl src\vdi_client.cpp   /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fovdi_client.obj
#       cl src\metrics.cpp      /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fometrics.obj
#       cl src\file_sink.cpp    /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fofile_sink.obj
#       cl src\buffer_pool.cpp  /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fobuffer_pool.obj
#       cl src\main.cpp         /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fomain.obj
#       cl src\fault_injector.cpp /c /EHsc /std:c++17 /Iinclude /Fofault_injector.obj
#       link *.obj /OUT:vdi_wrapper.exe ole32.lib /SUBSYSTEM:CONSOLE

# 17. include/metrics.h / src/metrics.cpp
#     - Metrics class tracks backup statistics:
#       * total_bytes_ (atomic uint64_t): running byte total
#       * chunk_count_ (atomic uint64_t): number of write chunks processed
#       * start_time_ (steady_clock::time_point): time of construction
#       * getcommand_latencies_, chunk_latencies_, completecommand_latencies_,
#         sink_latencies_ (vector<uint64_t>): timing distributions
#       * timings_ (vector<ChunkTiming>): full per-chunk breakdowns
#       * latency histogram buckets
#       * buffer pool accounting
#     - Public API:
#       * add_bytes(size), total_bytes() (added 2026-05-17 for stall detection)
#       * record_chunk_size(size), record_chunk_timing(ChunkTiming)
#       * record_chunk_latency, record_getcommand_latency (etc.)
#       * record_completecommand_latency, record_sink_latency
#       * record_buffer_acquire(bool), record_buffer_release()
#       * print_summary(), to_json()
#     - CPU utilization via GetProcessTimes (Windows-only)
#     - Per-stage latency breakdowns (P50/P95/P99) from ChunkTiming vector

# 18. include/sink.h
#     - Abstract Sink interface:
#       * virtual bool write(data, size) = 0
#       * virtual void flush() {}
#       * virtual bool is_open() const { return true; }  (added 2026-05-17)
#     - NullSink: discards all data, always returns true
#     - FileSink: Win32 WriteFile with aligned 1 MB buffer

# 19. include/file_sink.h / src/file_sink.cpp
#     - Win32 CreateFileW + WriteFile (no CRT iostream)
#     - 4096-byte aligned 1 MB write_buffer_ for batch coalescing
#     - Large writes (>= 1 MB) bypass buffer and WriteFile directly
#     - is_open() returns file_handle_ != INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE

# 20. include/buffer_pool.h / src/buffer_pool.cpp
#     - Pre-allocated pool of fixed-size buffers
#     - Thread-safe via std::mutex
#     - acquire(): returns buffer or nullptr if empty
#     - release(ptr): returns buffer to pool

# 21. include/logging.h
#     - Compile-time logging levels: OFF(0), INFO(1), DEBUG(2)
#     - LOG_ERROR, LOG_WARN (added 2026-05-17), LOG_INFO, LOG_DEBUG
#     - LOG_HRESULT macro for hex error code logging
#     - TRACE_EVENT RAII scope timer (DEBUG builds only)

# 22. include/chunk_timing.h
#     - Per-chunk timing breakdown struct:
#       size, getcommand_us, dispatch_us, sink_us, complete_us, total_us, timestamp_us

# 23. include/timer.h
#     - Abstract Timer interface with two backends
#     - ChronoTimer: portable std::chrono::steady_clock
#     - QPCTimer: Windows QueryPerformanceCounter

# 24. include/vdi_real.h
#     - Official MIDL-generated vdi.h from Microsoft SQL Server samples
#     - Reference only; actual interfaces defined in include/sqlvdi.h

# 25. Failure Handling / Robustness (Day 15, added 2026-05-17)
#     - Explicit SessionState machine guards all lifecycle transitions
#     - Graceful VD_E_CLOSE handling: flush sink → close devices → release COM
#     - Configurable GetCommand timeout (default 30s) instead of INFINITE
#     - Stall detection: warns after 60s no byte progress
#     - Sink failure propagation: write failures → SessionState::FAILED
#     - Defensive VDC_Write validation: null checks, size bounds
#     - Idempotent close(): double-close guard, destructor auto-cleanup
#     - HRESULT translation: hresult_to_string() for all VDI/COM errors
#     - Resource accounting: active buffers high-water mark
#     - Fault injection hooks for robustness testing
#     - See docs/operational-behavior.md for full documentation

# 26. Key docs
#     - docs/operational-behavior.md — State machine, shutdown, timeout, retry (2026-05-17)
#     - docs/benchmark-methodology.md — Benchmark workload + reproducibility
#     - docs/runtime-analysis.md — Runtime behavior (placeholder, needs data)
#     - docs/vdi-flow.md — VDI protocol lifecycle

# End of .clinerules